anding still? I still find my damage to be more while they are moving then when I use the regular shot, but when I try to use crit shot everytime the target gets out of distance or into melee range before they are ripped a new hole. Sucks that you can't automatically reload another crit shot. <br>  <br> Artifacts: <br> I have decided to get the following.: Gem Of Lost memories, Belt of the sun, Sharkskin Gloves, Golden Scarab Vest, Fools Bow &amp; Shades Of Mist. <br>  <br> ^^^ yay or nay to that list? <br>  <br> And of course if I decide to do ML's I will most likely be taking the Sojourner path. Battlemaster doesn't look that great. <br>  <br> Spellcrafting: <br> I assume the best thing to cap would be dex, con, qui, str, hits &amp; resists? <br>  <br> Alchemy: <br> I was thinking of putting a melee buffer shield on my chest &amp; legs, lifetap on my arms, haste on my hands &amp; feet. and undecided about the head piece. <br>  <br> ^^^ whatcha think? <br>  <br> umm, I can't think of anything else to ask at the moment. <br>  <br> Opinions &amp; suggestions wanted. <br> <p></p><span class="SignatureTitle">-----signature-----</span><div class="SignatureText">Boltzor Nukesem - 50 Wizard R4L4 <br> Direkt - 50 Scout R3L9 <br> Slurp Eee - 50 Necro R3L5 <br> Tifah - 50 Infiltrator R2 <br> Cleritic - 24 Heretic <img src="http://media.ign.com/boardfaces/59.gif" border="0" alt="dancing" hspace="0" vspace="0">  <br> </div></td></tr><tr align="right" valign="bottom"><td colspan=2 class="BoardRowB"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/post.asp?brd=20906&topic=78826278">Post Reply</a> | <a href="/active_topic_notify.asp?mes=78826278" class="BoardRowBLink">Active Topic Notification</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/pm_send.asp?usr=796580">Private Message</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/user_posts.asp?usr=796580">Post History</a></td></tr><tr align="left" valign="top" class="BoardRowA"><td class="BoardRowA" rowspan=3 width="17%"><a href=" http://users.ign.com/about/Nyctophobia?boards=vn " class="AuthorLink">Nyctophobia</a>&nbsp;<a href="/help/default.asp?goto=faqs%2Easp%23stars"><img align=absmiddle src=/images/star5.gif border=0 hspace=0 vspace=0 alt="7,171 posts"></a><br><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><!-- WISH & COLL STUFF --><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr class="BoardRowA"><td nowrap="false" class="BoardRowA"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/collection/Nyctophobia"><font size="1">collection (0)</font></a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/wishlist/Nyctophobia"><font size="1">wishlist (0)</font></a></td></tr></table><!-- /WISH & COLL STUFF	--><span style="font-weight: bold;">Posts:</span> 7,171<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Registered:</span> Apr 00<br></span><img border=0 hspace=8 vspace=8 src="http://media.ign.com/boards/images/icons/pimphat.gif" width="80" height="80" alt="5996" name="5996" id="5996" class="IconImage"><br></td><td class="BoardRowA" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Posted:</span>&nbsp;11/16/04 8:11am&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: bold;">Subject:</span> RE: Scouts...Scouts!...SCOUTS! - <span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Edited:</span>&nbsp;11/16/04 8:24am (2 edits total) <span style="font-weight: bold;">Edited By:</span> <a href=" http://users.ign.com/about/Nyctophobia?boards=vn " class="AuthorLink">Nyctophobia</a></td></tr><tr valign=top><td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%"><i>I'm quite a newbie to the class. So forgive me ahead of time if you may happy <br>  <br> First of all I am only level 42. Spec'd 42 bow, 18 slash, 30 stealth, 25 shield. <br>  <br> I plan to spec at level 50....50 bow, 21 slash, 42 shield, 33 stealth. <br>  <br> I don't plan to get into melee unless it's PvE basically. <br>  <br> Question on longbow: <br> 1) Rapid fire...is this supposed to reduce your damage output when active? <br>  <br> 2) choosing arrows...I know this is especially important, but I'm not sure which arrows work best against which class. (thrust&gt;chain, slash&gt;leather, crush&gt;plate....thats about all I know) <br>  <br> 3) Crit shot...is it true that this only works while the target is standing still? I still find my damage to be more while they are moving then when I use the regular shot, but when I try to use crit shot everytime the target gets out of distance or into melee range before they are ripped a new hole. Sucks that you can't automatically reload another crit shot. <br>  <br> Artifacts: <br> I have decided to get the following.: Gem Of Lost memories, Belt of the sun, Sharkskin Gloves, Golden Scarab Vest, Fools Bow &amp; Shades Of Mist. <br>  <br> ^^^ yay or nay to that list? <br>  <br> And of course if I decide to do ML's I will most likely be taking the Sojourner path. Battlemaster doesn't look that great. <br>  <br> Spellcrafting: <br> I assume the best thing to cap would be dex, con, qui, str, hits &amp; resists? <br>  <br> Alchemy: <br> I was thinking of putting a melee buffer shield on my chest &amp; legs, lifetap on my arms, haste on my hands &amp; feet. and undecided about the head piece. <br>  <br> ^^^ whatcha think? <br>  <br> umm, I can't think of anything else to ask at the moment. <br>  <br> Opinions &amp; suggestions wanted. </i> <br>  <br> I plan to spec at level 50....50 bow, 21 slash, 42 shield, 33 stealth. <br> I don't plan to get into melee unless it's PvE basically. <br> - You dont have a choice usually, theres no way to stop them without melee if they purge slam and you miss or they survive the FZ. <br>  <br> 1) Rapid fire...is this supposed to reduce your damage output when active? <br> - No, not really, I use RF every day, I open with crit, then do normal shots until they are low on HP, getting close to out of range or rushing me. Theres alot of clueless noobs that you'll find that run in circles when you shoot em. <br>  <br> 2) choosing arrows...I know this is especially important, but I'm not sure which arrows work best against which class. (thrust&gt;chain, slash&gt;leather, crush&gt;plate....thats about all I know) <br> - <a class=BoardRowBLink href="http://daoc.nisrv.com/modules.php?name=Armor_Resists">http://daoc.nisrv.com/modules.php?name=Armor_Resists</a> <br>  <br> 3) Crit shot...is it true that this only works while the target is standing still? I still find my damage to be more while they are moving then when I use the regular shot, but when I try to use crit shot everytime the target gets out of distance or into melee range before they are ripped a new hole. Sucks that you can't automatically reload another crit shot. <br> - Crits work on people backing up, strafing, stealthed forwards (with MOS2 or less), and FZed. Try loading a crit, hitting the fire button ONCE to auto shoot then hit crit and hit it once again, Ive gotten off as many as 4 crits on one (afk) target before they went down (DI3 ftw eh?). My scout has to get into melee with a good 50% of the people he pops with arrows but they dont last long getting into melee range with only 1-30% life. It gets really interesting when they blow IP then purge your slam, it turns into a really close fight unless you have FZ. <br>  <br> Artifacts: <br> I have decided to get the following.: Gem Of Lost memories, Belt of the sun, Sharkskin Gloves, Golden Scarab Vest, Fools Bow &amp; Shades Of Mist. <br> - GOLM is a must have imo 2% archery damage and range is awesome and recovory is a nice little bonus for PvE and RvR to get back into the fight quickly <br> - BotS is alright, I personally dont have it and wont get it, my guildie has it and swears by it, all personal preference. <br> - MSG are must have, period end of sentence. The arrows are too valuble to give up, they have great utility as well and the 3% archery speed and 3% range are nice as well <img src="http://media.ign.com/boardfaces/1.gif" border="0" alt="happy" hspace="0" vspace="0">  <br> - GSV I dont know why people would ever give this up, 3% perma melee resists, 4% archery damage, 4% archery range, and beetle bitch form.../drool <br> - Fools /puke, I personally have never used this bow, I dont see any reason why it exists...I might make a good bow for a merc or somthing but 4.8 speed, 18 dex and +5LB on your bow... thats just plain ugly. I have 3 friends that got Fool's Bow. Two of them retired it for PLAYER CRAFTED bows and one that got my current bow, the braggart's bow. Braggart's Bow is SUCH a better choice, the 5.4 speed is great, the arrows it summons makes tower defense a lil easier with the extra range and best of all is the +6 dex cap. <br> - SoM now this artifact I have little knowledge about. I just activated mine 2 days ago and have yet to start leveling it. My guildie that I duo with a little bit has it and loves it. Ive seen him take abuse from a SB/Hunter pet for over 30 seconds while I was dropping the hunter and he still came out alive and well without blowing IP. <br>  <br> And of course if I decide to do ML's I will most likely be taking the Sojourner path. Battlemaster doesn't look that great. <br> - Sojourner is the only ML path a scout should take. <br>  <br>  <br> Spellcrafting: <br> I assume the best thing to cap would be dex, con, qui, str, hits &amp; resists? <br>  <br> Obviously, but not possible. since you look like your going sniper spec Id suggest getting atleast 15 dex cap . If your going slash strength is important, Id suggest respeccing thrust but thats just me, assasians will own your already crappy weapon skill with str/con poisons and with thrust you atleast get damage benefit for high dex.  <br>  <br> Alchemy: <br> I was thinking of putting a melee buffer shield on my chest &amp; legs, lifetap on my arms, haste on my hands &amp; feet. and undecided about the head piece. <br> - Correct me if im wrong but you cant Alchy your chest if your wearing GSV, and you cant alchy your hands if you have MSG. But for your legs, arms and head Id either get DOT or Abla reactives, and for your boots get a str/con debuff charge. For your sword (if your going to use a PC sword) get DoT on it. And lastly for your sheild...Well I got a DD reactive, It helps against archers who decide to RF you, but unforunatly it goes off one in 100 blocks. If I had the chance to re alchy it Id have a abla proc on it. <br>  <br>  <br> Sorry its so long <img src="http://media.ign.com/boardfaces/2.gif" border="0" alt="sad" hspace="0" vspace="0">  <br> <p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr align="right" valign="bottom"><td colspan=2 class="BoardRowB"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/post.asp?brd=20906&topic=78826278">Post Reply</a> | <a href="/active_topic_notify.asp?mes=78827510" class="BoardRowBLink">Active Topic Notification</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/pm_send.asp?usr=20948">Private Message</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/user_posts.asp?usr=20948">Post History</a></td></tr><tr align="left" valign="top" class="BoardRowA"><td class="BoardRowA" rowspan=3 width="17%"><a href=" http://users.ign.com/about/Slurp_Eee?boards=vn " class="AuthorLink">Slurp_Eee</a>&nbsp;<a href="/help/default.asp?goto=faqs%2Easp%23stars"><img align=absmiddle src=/images/star4.gif border=0 hspace=0 vspace=0 alt="3,202 posts"></a><br><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><!-- WISH & COLL STUFF --><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr class="BoardRowA"><td nowrap="false" class="BoardRowA"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/collection/Slurp_Eee"><font size="1">collection (0)</font></a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="http://users.ign.com/wishlist/Slurp_Eee"><font size="1">wishlist (0)</font></a></td></tr></table><!-- /WISH & COLL STUFF	--><span style="font-weight: bold;">Posts:</span> 3,202<br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Registered:</span> Apr 03<br></span><br></td><td class="BoardRowA" colspan=2 width="83%"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Date Posted:</span>&nbsp;11/16/04 8:40am&nbsp;<span style="font-weight: bold;