 Yes, rapid fire will reduce the damage of the shot incremental to the cycle time reduction. (e.g., If the shoot time is 1/2, then so is damage done.) <br>  <br> &quot;2) choosing arrows...I know this is especially important, but I'm not sure which arrows work best against which class. (thrust&gt;chain, slash&gt;leather, crush&gt;plate....thats about all I know)&quot; <br> I have generally noticed that most players are weaker to crush. <br>  <br> &quot;3) Crit shot...is it true that this only works while the target is standing still? I still find my damage to be more while they are moving then when I use the regular shot, but when I try to use crit shot everytime the target gets out of distance or into melee range before they are ripped a new hole. Sucks that you can't automatically reload another crit shot.&quot; <br> A target moving forward cannot be crit shot, but straffing side to side and backwards movement can. Firing multiple crit shots is fairly easy. <br> <p></p><span class="SignatureTitle">-----signature-----</span><div class="SignatureText">Legatus - Paladin (50)  (LGM Armorer) <br> Legatin - Scout (50) <br> &lt;Plantagenet&gt; <br>  <br> </div></td></tr><tr align="right" valign="bottom"><td colspan=2 class="BoardRowB"><a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/post.asp?brd=20906&topic=78826278">Post Reply</a> | <a href="/active_topic_notify.asp?mes=78842342" class="BoardRowBLink">Active Topic Notification</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/pm_send.asp?usr=655176">Private Message</a> | <a class="BoardRowBLink" href="/user_posts.asp?usr=655176">Post History</a></td></tr><tr align="left" valign="top" class="BoardRowA"><td class="BoardRowA" rowspan=3 width="17%"><a href=" http://users.ign.com/about/DanthDH?boards=vn " class="AuthorLink">DanthDH</a>&nbsp;<a href="/help/default.asp?goto=faqs%2Easp%23stars"><img align=absmiddle src=/images/star3.gif border=0 hspace=0 vspace=0 alt="744 posts"></a><br><span style="font-size: 8pt;"><!-- WISH & COLL STUFF --><ta